<br>
Rules are:<br>
1st red scale defaulted to myself. If another happens to drop, then it will be rolled off to all bards and warriors level 50-52.<br>
<br>
If Paladin book drops, then all fallen paladins will be rezzed immidiatly, and then I will ask in raid 3 times for tells to be sent by paladins 50-52.<br>
<br>
1. Book of Scale - paladins 50-52<br>
2. Bladestopper - useable classes<br>
3. Blight, Hammer of Scourge - shaman<br>
4. Cloak of Flames - all melee but bards. In the event of the CoF but no drum or 2nd scale, bards will get in on roll.<br>
5. Gauntlet of Firey Might - all melee<br>
6. Gold Plated Koshigatana - all melee<br>
7. Heirophant's Crook - druid<br>
8. Orb of Tishan - all classes it can be used by <br>
9. Prayers of Life - all<br>
12. Selo's Drums of the March - Bards<br>
13. Treasure Hunters Satchel - Monks only<br>
<br>
I am planning on taking 5 groups of people, and would like 1 cleric for each group if possible. I'll need an experienced puller for the fire giants also. Minimum resists should be 60MR/70FR. <br>
Giant loot will be rolled separatly from dragon loot, at the end of the raid.<br>
<br>
I hope to see a good turnout, and I am anticipating seeing the dragon go down.<br>
